{
  "texts": [
    "The initial distribution µ 0 is absolutely continuous with respect to the Lebesgue measure (we still denote its density as µ 0) and there exists a positive constantC 0 such that (C 0) -1 ≤ µ 0 (x) ≤ C 0, ∀x ∈ Ω, and µ 0 ∈ C 2 (Ω); 2.For every T ≥ 0, the solution to (2.3), p t ∈ C 3 (Ω) for every t ≥ t 0 and there is a positive constantC * T such that (C * T) -1 ≤ p t (x) ≤ C * T, ∀x ∈ Ω, t ∈ [t 0, T]. 3.",
    "The velocity field f θ (•, •) ∈ C 2,1 (Ω × R, R d) for every θ ∈ Θ.",
    "For every T ≥ t 0, there is a positive constant C T such that sup θ∈Θ sup (x,t)∈Ω×[t0,T] |∇ • f θ (x, t)| ≤ C T.Remark 3.1.",
    "The Assumption 2-2 can be achieved under some mild conditions.",
    "For further details, we refer to [11,31] as references."
  ]
